api: hide request.user from api functions

Using request.user is not safe and insecure.  Authentication used should
be done by the api, not by Django.

Disallow this from api code to protect it from possible inadvertant use.

authz: AnonRead now shortcuts is_authorized() call on model if its a read request

This helps out is_authorized() method by not requiring unnecessary code
to test if the request is authenticated.

api: dont put schema below api, just make it the api endpoint

Makes more sense for clients.  Given an API base path (/api/v1/), you
make a request to that endpoint (given that you don't know that
/api/v1/schema/ without some more out of band information).  From there,
the api gives you everything you need via the schema.

Its not clear if we really need /schema/ endpoints for each resource.
Since the api schema dumps all of this at the moment.  Not sure why
you'd want to split it out?
